  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> has multiple pools of hit points, each of which is tracked separately. Damage and healing only applies to the currently active hit point pool. When a pool is depleted of all hit points, it becomes inactive. Only one pool can be active at any time. If a hit point pool is depleted, the <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> immediately saves against all ongoing conditions and effects. Any abilities which can reset do so. If all pools of hit points are inactive, <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> is killed. </p><p>If <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> takes a long rest, it fully heals the currently active pool and fully heals one depleted pool.</p>",
